From what I checked in EM's schema, "Label" seems not to be for this purpose (but for the Threshold in a multisensor type - is this correct?). Since the hwmonName is specific to Aspeed2600's chassis driver, I think I'd better change the Class to "Aspeed2600_Hwmon". The code before constructing objects will go as:
if ( "Class" == "Aspeed2600_Hwmon" || "Class" == "another hwmon driver" || ...)
{
  if ( "Class" == "Aspeed2600_Hwmon" )
  {
       hwmonName = "intrusion0_alarm";
  }
  else if
  {...}
  // create the hwmon class object with the hwmonName.
}
Any driver that wants to use the new sensor class can add its class name in the first if condition and provide its hwmonName to the constructor. Then, users can just choose the driver without knowing about the hwmonName.

Do you think this is a good way to go?
